entry.title: Lovro Šitović (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Lovro Šitović, a 17th-century Croatian Franciscan friar who wrote a Latin grammar, was a convert from Islam?

entry.title: Jade Armor (Wikipedia — did you know?)

entry.title: Tchinda Andrade (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that trans women in Cape Verde are colloquially referred to as tchindas, named after Tchinda Andrade, the first trans woman in the country to come out publicly?

entry.title: gogi-guksu (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the dish gogi-guksu, from South Korea's Jeju Island, developed in part because of the Japanese colonial period?

entry.title: So Sethaputra (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that So Sethaputra compiled his authoritative English–Thai dictionary while in prison, with the manuscripts smuggled out for publication?

entry.title: Fran Foley (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that after being named the general manager of the Minnesota Vikings for three years, Fran Foley served in the position for just three months?
